41:31.458 --> 41:34.083
-What's your cure for hangovers?
-Hangover?

41:34.166 --> 41:35.166
Recently…

41:36.875 --> 41:39.041
-I've been eating porridge.
-Porridge?

41:39.125 --> 41:41.291
Or I'd get a burger.

41:42.375 --> 41:44.541
In my day,
we ate jjajangmyeon to look cool.

41:44.625 --> 41:46.750
-You know what?
-What?

41:46.833 --> 41:51.041
There's a world famous beverage
that's known to cure hangovers.

41:51.791 --> 41:52.750
It's called IdH.

41:53.458 --> 41:55.875
-I, D…
-IdH.

41:55.958 --> 41:59.583
When you write IdH,
what does it look like?

42:01.875 --> 42:03.500
-I, D, H?
-It's funny.

42:03.583 --> 42:09.166
-Try writing IdH like this.
-I see, IdH.

42:10.250 --> 42:11.583
What's that in Korean?

42:13.083 --> 42:15.208
IdH.

42:17.041 --> 42:18.625
-Dae?
-Bae.

42:19.291 --> 42:20.208
"Bae"?

42:20.291 --> 42:23.000
IdH. It looks like "Bae" in Korean.

42:23.500 --> 42:25.958
-Bae, as in "pear."
-That's correct.

42:28.375 --> 42:31.875
You know the crushed pear juice?

42:31.958 --> 42:35.166
That's my go-to hangover drink.

42:35.250 --> 42:36.083
Many of us do.

42:36.666 --> 42:39.458
But it's become famous
even outside of Korea

42:39.541 --> 42:42.291
as a magical hangover cure.

42:42.375 --> 42:45.291
Foreign pears taste
nothing like Korean pears.

42:45.375 --> 42:48.291
Australia is
the biggest importer of Korean pears.

42:48.375 --> 42:51.916
And they tested to see
whether it can really cure hangovers.

42:52.000 --> 42:53.916
It's actually high in asparagine.

42:54.000 --> 42:58.291
A foreign magazine tested it to see
whether it helps treat hangovers.

42:58.375 --> 43:00.750
It turns out, it's really effective.

